On October 9th, Leif Erikson Day is celebrated in honor of the Viking explorer who sailed across the Atlantic in search of new lands over a thousand years ago. Leif Erikson's spirit of exploration, courage, and faith continues to inspire Americans today. This proclamation recognizes the strong bonds between Americans and the homelands of the Vikings, including Denmark, Finland, Iceland, Norway, and Sweden. It also acknowledges the contributions of Nordic Americans to the United States and encourages Americans to celebrate their achievements and cultural traditions.